               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440506-name-520" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-520" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-520" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440506-name-520" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY ADAMS</persName>
                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">dressmaker, Butler's-buildings, East Smithfield.</hi> Between six and seven o'clock in the evening of the 2nd of May I was in Aldgate—I saw the prisoner's hand drawing a purse from my pocket—it contained one sovereign, two half-crowns, thirteen shillings, and two groats—he ran off, and I lost sight of him—I was kicked by a person—I saw the prisoner go as far as the <hi rend="italic">cabs</hi> near Aldgate church.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440506-name-521" type="witnessName">
